  &lt;p id="MENeQY"&gt;The dust is still settling from &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/9/24237601/apple-iphone-16-event-announcements-products"&gt;Apple’s latest iPhone event&lt;/a&gt;, which introduced us to the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24236958/apple-watch-series-10-hands-on-bigger-brighter-and-thinner"&gt;Apple Watch Series 10&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/9/24239947/apple-airpods-4-hands-on-preview-features-anc"&gt;new set of AirPods&lt;/a&gt;, and a suite of smartphones that are due to arrive later this month. And while we’ve only had some initial hands-on time with the new iPhone 16 models, preorders are now open.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="6eR8ej"&gt;Apple’s latest phones — specifically the iPhone 16, 16 Plus, 16 Pro, and 16 Pro Max — are set to arrive on September 20th. They introduce new processors and a slick new Camera Control button, but none of them look to be a drastic overhaul of last year’s iPhone 15 series. That being said, perhaps things will get interesting when Apple Intelligence comes to the new models with the release of iOS 18.1 beta in October.&lt;/p&gt;
