  &lt;p id="s8HpBg"&gt;The Netflix app is dropping support for older iPhones and iPads that are stuck at iOS 16. &lt;a href="https://9to5mac.com/2024/09/12/netflix-older-iphone-ipad/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;9to5Mac &lt;/em&gt;reports that&lt;/a&gt; Netflix is showing an alert to users on some iOS 16 devices that says “We’ve updated the Netflix app! To use the latest version, install iOS 17 or later.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="PgAT9Z"&gt;The change only impacts devices that can’t be updated to iOS 17, such as the iPhone X, iPhone 8, and iPhone 8 Plus handsets, and Apple’s first-generation iPad Pro and iPad 5 tablets. These devices will be unable to receive further Netflix updates, such as important patches for bugs and other security concerns. Apple is rolling out iOS 18 on September 16th.&lt;/p&gt;
